title: For Sale:  Ammo and Gun Prices
postcontent:
Sellers:  Fact - If you are listing your ammo and guns here you want to either make a profit, or come out on top of a trade.  Feel free to add on your gas used driving around to scrounge up everything you find, and I bet your listing time is worth $20/hour.  There is no reason to get evil when someone disagrees with you.  If your .22 - .500S&W is worth the price...then keep listing it and buying more to list that too.  At some point, you will either get tired of what you are doing or be a millionaire.  Good Luck

Buyers:  Fact - If you know what something is worth, and you see it listed too high...flag it, or just move on.  If you choose to buy something overpriced, that is your choice.  Don't bitch about it.  Do not be surprised when ammo manufactures decide to shelf price ammo at double or triple todays price to match what it is on armslist.com, gunbroker.com and other sites.  When this happens, your $60 brick of .22 ammo will be closer to $250+ on here.  Good luck with that.

title: For Sale:  J.C. Higgs (Sears and Roebuck) Model 30 (made by High Standard)
postcontent: Offered is my J.C. Higgins .22 semi auto rifle in Excellent Condition. I am selling many of my unused guns as I approach retirement and relocation, this rifle is from my collection of 1950s and 1960s era .22 rifles, the kind I used to wish I had when I was a kid in those days and saw them advertised in the outdoors magazines and catalogs, and when I saw them in hardware stores and the sporting goods section at Montgomery Wards and Sears and Roebuck. When I started collecting this type of rifle, I only bought the best examples I could find. This rifle was made my High Standard for sale by Sears and Roebuck under their house name of J.C. Higgin; this was the era prior to Sears branding their firearms with the Ted Williams name. This rifle has a highly unusual feature of having a spring loaded retractable sling built into the stock that pulls out to connect to a lug under the front of the barrel and then retracts back into the stock for a flush fit; it is very unusual to find one of these rifles with the original sling intact and working, collectors take note; I have never seen another J.C. Higgins Model 30 with the sling present and functional like this rifle has. This rifle is in Excellent condition with beautiful 2 piece Walnut stock and very nice original blue finish with no rust and all functions are correct. I've only shot it 50 times when I got it for a function assurance check, it shot fine; then I cleaned it and put it in a gunsock and into my climatically controlled vault where it has sat untouched for years. Heck of a nice rifle and a real treasure from a bygone era. I will meet buyer half way between us for a FTF cash and carry deal at a public place during daylight hours. I am not interested in trades or counter offers, buyer must be legal Maryland resident or active duty military stationed in Maryland, I will not ship this rifle. thanks for looking, pls email with any questions. Pls check out my other listings on Armslist.
